From: Vladimir Skvortsov <vskvortsov@emcraft.com>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] torizon: restore distro boot_targets on lec-mtk-i1200

The Adlink board-support patch (0001-Added-Board-support-for-LEC-MTK-i1200)
repoints BOOTENV_BOOT_TARGETS to a single "embedded" target - a signed boot
script compiled into the U-Boot binary that loaded a fitImage from a raw
"kernel" GPT partition.

Common Torizon OS has no such partition: the kernel/DTB/initramfs live inside
the OSTree deployment on the rootfs partition, and U-Boot is expected to scan
the storage device, find the bootable rootfs partition and source Torizon's
/boot.scr (which imports the OSTree-managed /boot/loader/uEnv.txt). Revert the
vendor change so distro_bootcmd expands boot_targets to the upstream
auto-generated device list (scsiN/usbN) again.

Signed-off-by: Vladimir Skvortsov <vskvortsov@emcraft.com>
---
 include/config_distro_bootcmd.h | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/include/config_distro_bootcmd.h b/include/config_distro_bootcmd.h
--- a/include/config_distro_bootcmd.h
+++ b/include/config_distro_bootcmd.h
@@ -421,7 +421,7 @@
 #define BOOTENV_DEV_NAME(devtypeu, devtypel, instance, ...) \
 	BOOTENV_DEV_NAME_##devtypeu(devtypeu, devtypel, instance, ## __VA_ARGS__)
 #define BOOTENV_BOOT_TARGETS \
-	"boot_targets=embedded\0"
+	"boot_targets=" BOOT_TARGET_DEVICES(BOOTENV_DEV_NAME) "\0"

 #define BOOTENV_DEV(devtypeu, devtypel, instance, ...) \
 	BOOTENV_DEV_##devtypeu(devtypeu, devtypel, instance, ## __VA_ARGS__)
